Recently OpenAI added an additional memory feature called &ldquo;chat history&rdquo;, which allows ChatGPT to reference past conversations. The details of the implementation are not known. The documentation highlights that: &ldquo;It uses this to learn about your interests and preferences, helping make future chats more personalized and relevant.&rdquo;
I decided to spend some time to figure out how it works.
Update: Video Tutorial Added Based on the interest in this post, I&rsquo;ve also created a video tutorial.

Revisiting Cookie Crimes In 2018 @mangopdf described &ldquo;Cookie Crimes&rdquo;, which is great research around Chrome&rsquo;s remote debugging feature that allows adversaries and malware to gain access to cookies quite convienently during post-exploitation.
The original research is published here, and it still works today.
The new Microsoft Edge browser and Chromium Microsoft&rsquo;s latest Edge browser is based on the same code, Chromium. I guess, you already know where this is going now&hellip;
